rd <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Le","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Lewis   or respelling of   Lou  , as borne by the impresario  Lew Grade  (  1906–98 , originally  Louis Winogradsky )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Gros","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old Norse personal name, possibly derived from Norse <i>gróa</i> ‘to grow’, or possibly related to the Celtic element <i>gruach</i> ‘woman’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Geoffrey Le Gros of Crostwick was born in 1210, in England, United Kingdom as the son of Hugh Le Gros. He had at least 3 sons. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"1210–":"1210–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1276–Male":"1276–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1310":"1310","1210":"1210","1276":"1276","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1180":"1180","England, UK":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1210–":"1210–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1276–Male":"1276–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1310":"1310","1210":"1210","1276":"1276","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1180":"1180","England, UK":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1210–":"1210–Décédé","1210–Male":